# Monorepo Structure (Turborepo + pnpm)
- Use Turborepo for build orchestration and caching
- Leverage pnpm workspaces for dependency management
- Configure proper task dependencies in turbo.json
- Use shared configurations where possible
- Implement proper package versioning strategy

# Documentation
- Use JSDoc comments for all public APIs
- Include usage examples in documentation
- Document complex business logic
- Keep README files up to date
- Document API endpoints with Swagger/OpenAPI

# Git Practices
- Leave commiting and interaction with remote repository to the user, only suggest commit messages
- Keep commit messages suggestion short but descriptive

# Code Reviews
- Review for architectural decisions
- Check for proper error handling
- Verify test coverage
- Ensure documentation is updated
- Check for proper React Query usage patterns

# Monitoring & Logging
- Implement proper logging strategies
- Use structured logging
- Monitor performance metrics
- Implement proper error tracking

- Track React Query cache performance

# Running commands
- This is a Turbo monorepo utilizing pnpm. So only ever use pnpm (or npx) to run relevant commands.
